\boxed{42} Julie read 12 pages yesterday and twice as many today, which means she read \(2 \times 12 = 24\) pages today. So, the total number of pages she has read so far is \(12 + 24 = 36\) pages.

The book has 120 pages in total, so the remaining pages are \(120 - 36 = 84\) pages.

If she wants to read half of the remaining pages tomorrow, she should read \(\frac{84}{2} = 42\) pages. \boxed{42}
